.TH "rxrpc_kernel_set_max_life" 9 "rxrpc_kernel_set_max_life" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rxrpc_kernel_set_max_life \- Set maximum lifespan on a call
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rxrpc_kernel_set_max_life
.BI "(struct socket *sock "  ","
.BI "struct rxrpc_call *call "  ","
.BI "unsigned long hard_timeout "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sock" 12
The socket the call is on
.IP "call" 12
The call to configure
.IP "hard_timeout" 12
The maximum lifespan of the call in jiffies
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set the maximum lifespan of a call.  The call will end with ETIME or
ETIMEDOUT if it takes longer than this.
